## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="15b52-141">Poniższy przykład tworzy gramatyki, który rozpoznaje frazę "kraj, który wygrała świata w piłce nożnej" następuje nazwa kraju, która została wybrana świata w piłce nożnej.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-141">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-142">W przykładzie jest tworzony publiczny reguły o nazwie `WorldCupWinner`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-142">The example creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-143">Przykład tworzy następnie dwóch <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> obiektów `ruleEurope` i `ruleSAmerica`, przekazując <xref:System.String> dla identyfikatora reguły i <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsElement> tablica zawierająca <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> obiektu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-143">The example then creates two <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> objects, `ruleEurope` and  `ruleSAmerica`, passing in a <xref:System.String> for the rule identifier and an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsElement> array containing a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-144">Następnie w przykładzie dodano reguły odniesienia do `ruleEurope` i `ruleSAmerica` z reguły `WorldCupWinner`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-144">Subsequently, the example adds rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica` from the rule `WorldCupWinner`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  // Create a grammar from an SRGSDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument srgsGrammar = new SrgsDocument ();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule ("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add (new SrgsItem ("A nation that has won the world cup is"));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the grammar and make winnerRule  
  // the root rule of the grammar.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  srgsGrammar.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="15b52-145">Utworzono gramatyki ma następującą postać.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-145">The created grammar has the following form.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<grammar version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar" root="WorldCupWinner">  
    <rule id="WorldCupWinner" scope="public">  
        <item> A nation that has won the world cup is </item>  
        <one-of>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#EuropeanNations" />  
            </item>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#SouthAmericanNations" />  
            </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="EuropeanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> England </item>  
            <item> France </item>  
            <item> Germany </item>  
            <item> Italy </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="SouthAmericanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> Argentina </item>  
            <item> Brazil </item>  
            <item> Uruguay </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
</grammar>  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="15b52-153">Typowe dodatki do <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> obejmują obiektu <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>, i <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> obiekty, które określają, co powiedzieć głośników.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-153">Typical additions to an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object include <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsItem>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef>, and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> objects that specify what speakers can say.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-154">Element prawidłowa reguła musi zawierać co najmniej jeden fragment tekstu rozpoznawalnych lub jedno odwołanie do reguły.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-154">A valid rule element must contain at least one piece of recognizable text or one rule reference.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-155">Zobacz [tworzenie SrgsGrammar przy użyciu Gramatyk](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361680(v%3doffice.14)) Aby uzyskać więcej informacji.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-155">See [Create Grammars Using SrgsGrammar](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361680(v%3doffice.14)) for more information.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="15b52-156"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> Obiektu może również zawierać <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> i <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> obiektów, które dodać semantyki wartości i kluczy semantycznego reguły.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-156">An <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object may also contain <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> objects that add semantic values and semantic keys to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-157">Aparat rozpoznawania mowy zwróci informacji semantycznych, a także frazy rozpoznawanym po rozpoznaniu frazę.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-157">The speech recognition engine will return the semantic information, as well as the recognized phrase, when it recognizes the phrase.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-158">Zobacz [semantycznego znaczników interpretacji](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361595(v%3doffice.14)) Aby uzyskać więcej informacji.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-158">See [Semantic Interpretation Markup](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/office/developer/speech-technologies/hh361595(v%3doffice.14)) for more information.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="15b52-159">Poniższy przykład tworzy gramatyki, który rozpoznaje frazę "kraj, który wygrała świata w piłce nożnej" następuje nazwa kraju, która została wybrana świata w piłce nożnej.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-159">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-160">Po utworzeniu <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> obiektu `winnerRule` i identyfikator ciągu `WorldCupWinner`, w przykładzie użyto <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> metody Dołącz ciąg "kraj, który wygrała świata w piłce nożnej is" do reguły.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-160">After creating the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object `winnerRule` and giving it the string identifier `WorldCupWinner`, the example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method to append the string  "A nation that has won the World Cup is" to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-161">Przykład tworzy następnie dwie dodatkowe reguły, `ruleEurope` i `ruleSAmerica`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-161">The example then creates two additional rules, `ruleEurope` and  `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-162">Ponownie, używając <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> metoda, przykład dołącza <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> obiekt `WorldCupWinner` regułę, która zawiera odwołania do reguły do `ruleEurope` i `ruleSAmerica`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-162">Again using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Add%2A> method, the example appends an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> object to the `WorldCupWinner` rule that contains rule references to `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
// and set its scope to public.  
SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
// Add the introduction.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
// Create the rule for the European nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
// Create the rule for the South American nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
// Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
// Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
// the root rule of the document.  
document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
document.Root = winnerRule;  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="15b52-192">Wartość domyślna dla zakresu to `Private`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-192">The default value for scope is `Private`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-193">Reguła prywatnej można uaktywniać tylko rozpoznawania przez odwołanie reguły z reguły głównego w jego zawierającego gramatyki lub inną regułę, która odwołuje się do reguły głównego.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-193">A private rule can only be activated for recognition by a rule reference from the root rule in its containing grammar or from another rule that is referenced from the root rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-194">Prywatne reguły nie może odwoływać się zewnętrznych gramatykę, chyba że prywatnej reguły jest zadeklarowany jako reguły głównego jego zawierającego gramatyki.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-194">A private rule cannot be referenced by an external grammar, unless the private rule is declared as the root rule of its containing grammar.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="15b52-195">Jeśli ustawiono zakres `Public`, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> obiektu można aktywować rozpoznawania odwołania z <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> obiektu w gramatyce zawierającego lub przy użyciu reguły w gramatyce zewnętrznych.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-195">If its scope is set to `Public`, an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object can be activated for recognition by a reference from a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> object in the containing grammar or from a rule in an external grammar.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="15b52-196">Poniższy przykład tworzy gramatyki, który rozpoznaje frazę "kraj, który wygrała świata w piłce nożnej" następuje nazwa kraju, która została wybrana świata w piłce nożnej.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-196">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="15b52-197">Tworzy regułę publicznego o nazwie `WorldCupWinner` i ustawia zakres tej reguły na wartość publiczne.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-197">It creates a public rule named `WorldCupWinner` and sets the scope of that rule to Public.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule and set its scope to public.  
SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
// Add the introduction.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
// Create the rule for the European nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"), new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
// Create the rule for the South American nations.  
SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"), new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
// Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope)), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica)})));  
  
// Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
// the root rule of the document.  
document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
document.Root = winnerRule;  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="15b52-198">Utworzono gramatyki ma następującą postać.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="15b52-198">The created grammar has the following form.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<grammar version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar" root="WorldCupWinner">  
    <rule id="WorldCupWinner" scope="public">  
        <item> A nation that has won the world cup is </item>  
        <one-of>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#EuropeanNations" />  
            </item>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#SouthAmericanNations" />  
            </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="EuropeanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> England< /item>  
            <item> France </item>  
            <item> Germany </item>  
            <item> Italy </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="SouthAmericanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> Argentina </item>  
            <item> Brazil </item>  
            <item> Uruguay </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
</grammar>  
```
